lly excited CO in the\nfollowing reaction steps: CO + h{\\nu}->CO*, CO* + H2->HCO + H where newly\nformed H-atoms are then available for further hydrogenation reactions. The HCO\nformation yields have a strong temperature dependence for the investigated\nregime, which is most likely linked to the H2 sticking coefficient. Finally,\nthe astronomical relevance of this photo-induced reaction channel is discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Sep 2018 13:24:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-28"}
